        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:18PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Alexander Stephens
Park, or over Crawfordville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Crawfordville, Sharon, Robinson, Lyneville, Alexander Stephens Park,
Sandy Cross, Carters Grove, and Daniel Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
